comparisons_table <- read.table(comparisons_file, header = TRUE)
seuset <- SetIdent(seuset, value = cluster_annotation)
DE_results_list <- list()
DE_results_TF_list <- list()

for (i in rownames(comparisons_table)){
  print(i)
  print(comparisons_table[i,][["AM_cluster"]])
  AM_clust <- comparisons_table[i,][["AM_cluster"]]
  VM_clust <- comparisons_table[i,][["VM_cluster"]]
  comparison_id <- paste0(VM_clust, "vs", AM_clust)
  DE_results <- FindMarkers(seuset, ident.1 = VM_clust, ident.2 = AM_clust, min.pct = min_pct_exp)
  DE_results <- DE_results[DE_results$p_val_adj < pval_adj_tresh,]
  
  # Order on LogFC
  DE_results <- DE_results[order(DE_results$avg_log2FC, decreasing = TRUE),]
  write.csv(DE_results, paste0("DE-genes_", cluster_annotation,"_", comparison_id, "_pct", min_pct_exp, ".csv"), quote = FALSE)
  DE_results_list[[comparison_id]] <- DE_results
  
  # Selecting TFs in the DE-gene lists
  DE_results_TF <- DE_results[rownames(DE_results) %in% tf_vector,]
  write.csv(DE_results_TF, paste0("DE-TFs_", cluster_annotation,"_", comparison_id, "_pct", min_pct_exp, ".csv"), quote = FALSE)
  DE_results_TF_list[[comparison_id]] <- DE_results_TF
  
}

Generate heatmaps for TF

## Settings for the output PDFs
hg_pdf = 8
wd_pdf = 10
col_ft_size = 8
row_ft_size = 8

ht_list <- list()
hclust_list <- list()
n_split_TF <- 11

for (q in c("TF")){
  ## Change split-settings according to the gene set:
  if (q == "TF"){
    n_split <- n_split_TF
    unique_DE_subset <- unique_DE_TF
  }
  
  ## Generate matrix of averages: 
  avg_express <- AverageExpression(seuset, 
                    assays = "sf",
                    features = unique_DE_subset,
                    group.by = variables_to_average,
                    slot = "data")
  avg_express <- as.matrix(avg_express[["sf"]])
  
  ## Manually set order of columns:
  starting_columns <- grep("shared", colnames(avg_express), value = TRUE)
  order_columns <- c(starting_columns, colnames(avg_express)[!colnames(avg_express) %in% starting_columns])
  avg_express <- avg_express[,order_columns]
  
  ## Row-Scaling of the averages:
  avg_express_scaled <- t(scale(t(avg_express)))
  
  ht_list[[paste0("avg_", q)]] <- Heatmap(avg_express, 
            row_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = row_ft_size),
            column_title = paste0("Average expression"),
            column_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = col_ft_size),
            cluster_columns = FALSE,
            column_gap = unit(1, "mm")
            )
  
  ht_list[[paste0("scaled_", q)]] <- Heatmap(avg_express_scaled,
          split = n_split,
          column_title = paste0("Scaled average expression"), 
          row_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = row_ft_size),
          column_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = col_ft_size),
          cluster_columns = FALSE,
          column_gap = unit(1, "mm")
          )
  
  ## retrieve gene hierarchical clustering:
  ht <- draw(ht_list[[paste0("scaled_", q)]])
  list_of_geneclusters <- row_order(ht)
  list_of_geneclusters <- as.list(list_of_geneclusters)
  tmp <- as.data.frame(avg_express_scaled)
  
  for (i in 1:n_split){
    print(i)
    genes_incluster <- as.data.frame(list_of_geneclusters[[i]])
    colnames(genes_incluster) <- "gene_id"
    genes_incluster$gene <- rownames(tmp)[list_of_geneclusters[[i]]]
    list_of_geneclusters[[i]] <- genes_incluster
  }
  
  hclust_list[[paste0("scaled_", q)]] <- list_of_geneclusters
}

Feature plots per gene cluster:

for (gene_subset in names(hclust_list)){
  ## Generate seperate folders for the feature plots per gene clusters:
  system(paste0("mkdir -p ", "FeaturePlots_", gsub("scaled_", "", gene_subset)))
  
  df_hclust <- data.frame(matrix(ncol = 2, nrow = 0))
  colnames(df_hclust) <- c("gene", "cluster")

  for (i in 1:length(list_of_geneclusters)){
    ## Generate a df for writing to file
    tmp_df <- as.data.frame(hclust_list[[gene_subset]][[i]]$gene)
    tmp_df$cluster <- i 
    colnames(tmp_df) <- c("gene", "cluster")
    df_hclust <- rbind(df_hclust, tmp_df)
    
    ## Generate featureplots for the genes per gene-cluster
    p <- FeaturePlot(seuset, features = hclust_list[[gene_subset]][[i]]$gene, combine = FALSE) 
    
    
    for(q in 1:length(p)) {
      p[[q]] <- p[[q]] & NoAxes() #  + NoLegend()
    }
    
    n_vplots <- ceiling(length(p) / 2)
    
    pdf(paste0("FeaturePlots_", gsub("scaled_", "", gene_subset), "/GeneCluster", i,".pdf"), width = 10, height = (5*n_vplots))
    print(cowplot::plot_grid(plotlist = p, ncol = 2))
    dev.off()
    
    # FeaturePlot(seuset, features = list_of_geneclusters[[i]]$gene, split.by = "Experiment")
  }
